The problem requires finding the minimum number of characters to be removed from the string to achieve a string with no repeated characters. We can solve this problem using nested loops to iterate through the string and compare adjacent characters. If they are equal, we update the result variable with the minimum of the current length of the string minus the indices of the characters. Finally, return the result.

The time complexity is O(n^2) because we have two nested loops iterating through the string. The space complexity is O(1) as we only use a single variable for the result. The energy implications are low because the algorithm only performs simple comparisons and updates, which are energy-efficient operations.

